This course in an exploration of the family of musical idioms called jazz. Attention will be given to issues of style, to selected musicians, and to the social, cultural, and scholarly issues raised by its study.&#8232;

&#8232;Several students commented that this course was interesting and engaging, and also that it was “straightforward” and they learned a lot from it. However, a few other students mentioned that the course was difficult and, at times, unclear. &#8232;

Most students found Professor Ramsey enthusiastic, knowledgeable, and a great lecturer. One student also commented that Professor Ramsey was “often hard to reach,” while a couple of students described Professor Ramsey as disorganized. A few students also mentioned that Professor Ramsey was often too self-promoting. 

&#8232;Many students who commented said they would recommend this course to anyone who was interested in music and jazz, but several students also mentioned that this course “requires more background knowledge than the description indicates.” A few students also mentioned that the assigned readings seemed pointless and irrelevant to the course.
